Vendo is for zerkers. Our answer to that is DT (even if it is odd).<br>
<br>
I dunno. I'm still in confusion as to what i'd really want my special RA to be. I'm not to keen with any of these suggestions so far (Maybe i'm just picky, or don't care enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START  >D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/grin.gif ALT=" >D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Not to say the suggestions so far are falty or 'useless', I just don't take to them eagerly). While they all sound usefull, none of these really &quot;stick out&quot; to me. I want something to make me think &quot;No one else in the field can do this&quot;. A real uniqe RA, not some copied ability that does something similer to anothers. I'm not even very partial to my suggestion (figured it was something along the lines of our armsman counter-part).<br>
<br>
I do have a question for you guys though; would you consider the Mercenary to have an understanding (a feint one, i'd imagin) of Chi? (Those of you who don't know or want a clear definition, Chi is the vital force believed in Taoism and other Chinese beliefs thought to be inherent in all things. The unimpeded circulation of chi and a balance of its negative and positive forms in the body are held to be essential to good health in traditional Chinese medicine. Often, in fantasy settings, this 'chi' is used to form destructive waves, balls, or some sort of physically measureable object with results in destruction - Sometimes it's used for positive things like healing-.)  I'v been trying to think of how we &quot;flurry&quot;. It's one attack that just happens out of the blue. What causes us to have this extreme, unavoidable hit? I was thinking if the use (a beginners use) of Chi fueled us to swing one always-hitting swip every two minutes, then perhaps we could dive deeper into it and call apon it's use further?<br>
<br>
This could open up potential ideas (Though I hope people refrain from asking for a Super Sayian ability <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). I'd like to know what mythic and others consider our stance on this. I can see it as being too out of a mercs grasp.. But I also see it as being something a merc finds.<br>
<br>
After all, we don't follow a god. We go by our pocketbook, and look in ourselves for strength (roleplay wise, anyways). We should find this interesting source of power sooner or later, i'd imagine.. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
